        {
            "anchor": "medicinal_plants",
			"type": "patchouli:spotlight",
            "item": {
                "tag": "tfg:medicinal_ingredients/plants"
            },
            "title": "Medicinal Plants",
            "text": "Many plants in $(bold)$(#ff0fb7)TerraFirma$()$()$(bold)$(#595959)Greg$()$() hold medicinal value and can be used for creating phytotherapeutic medicine. You can combine these ingredients in a mixing bowl with wax, binders, and spring water to make pills. Or more advanced medications."
        },
        {
            "title": "Spices",
			"type": "patchouli:spotlight",
            "item": {
                "tag": "tfg:foods/spice_plants"
            },
            "anchor": "spices",
			"text": "With $(thing)Firmalife$(), there are a number of small plants you can collect and grow on your own, which have cooking properties. They can all be found in the wild, and once harvested, may be cultivated in a $(l:firmalife/greenhouse)Greenhouse$(), in which they consume 20 points of N, P, and K."
		},
